## Q5 — CPU Scheduling (Round Robin, Quantum = 3)

### What is being asked?
4 render jobs all arrive at t=0. Time quantum = 3ms. Simulate Round Robin scheduling. Find which job finishes first and average turnaround time.

### What is Round Robin?
Every process gets a small fixed time slot (quantum = 3ms). After its turn, it goes back to the end of the queue. Like a merry-go-round — everyone gets equal turns.

### Input:
| Job | Burst Time |
|-----|-----------|
| J1 | 10 |
| J2 | 4 |
| J3 | 6 |
| J4 | 3 |

All arrive at t=0. Quantum = 3.

---

### FILE: `round_robin.c`

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int n = 4;
    int quantum = 3;

    int pid[]         = {1, 2, 3, 4};
    int burst[]       = {10, 4, 6, 3};
    int remaining[]   = {10, 4, 6, 3};  // Copy of burst — we'll decrement this
    int arrival[]     = {0, 0, 0, 0};   // All arrive at t=0
    int ct[4]         = {0};             // Completion time
    int finished[4]   = {0};            // Has the process finished?

    int current_time = 0;
    int done = 0;     // Count of finished processes

    printf("Round Robin Scheduling (Quantum = %d)\n", quantum);
    printf("========================================\n");
    printf("Gantt Chart execution:\n");

    // Keep running until all processes are done
    while (done < n) {
        int any_ran = 0;   // Track if at least one process ran this cycle

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (remaining[i] > 0) {
                any_ran = 1;

                // This process runs for min(quantum, remaining) time
                int run_time = (remaining[i] < quantum) ? remaining[i] : quantum;

                printf("Time %2d - %2d : J%d runs (remaining after = %d)\n",
                       current_time, current_time + run_time,
                       pid[i], remaining[i] - run_time);

                current_time  += run_time;
                remaining[i]  -= run_time;

                // Check if this process just finished
                if (remaining[i] == 0 && !finished[i]) {
                    ct[i] = current_time;
                    finished[i] = 1;
                    done++;
                    printf("  --> J%d FINISHED at time %d\n", pid[i], ct[i]);
                }
            }
        }

        // Safety: if nothing ran, break (shouldn't happen in normal cases)
        if (!any_ran) break;
    }

    // Calculate and print TAT and WT
    printf("\nResults:\n");
    printf("%-5s %-5s %-5s %-5s %-5s %-5s\n", "Job", "BT", "CT", "TAT", "WT", "");

    float total_tat = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        int tat = ct[i] - arrival[i];  // Turnaround = Completion - Arrival
        int wt  = tat - burst[i];      // Waiting = TAT - Burst
        total_tat += tat;
        printf("J%-4d %-5d %-5d %-5d %-5d\n", pid[i], burst[i], ct[i], tat, wt);
    }

    printf("\nAverage Turnaround Time = %.2f\n", total_tat / n);

    // Find which job finished first
    int first_finish_time = ct[0];
    int first_job = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if (ct[i] < first_finish_time) {
            first_finish_time = ct[i];
            first_job = i;
        }
    }
    printf("Job that finished FIRST: J%d at time %d\n", pid[first_job], first_finish_time);

    return 0;
}
```

---

### Manual Trace (Queue cycles):

**Queue: J1, J2, J3, J4**

| Time | Running | Remaining after |
|------|---------|----------------|
| 0-3 | J1 | J1=7 |
| 3-6 | J2 | J2=1 |
| 6-9 | J3 | J3=3 |
| 9-12 | J4 | J4=0 ✓ DONE at t=12 |
| 12-15 | J1 | J1=4 |
| 15-16 | J2 | J2=0 ✓ DONE at t=16 |
| 16-19 | J3 | J3=0 ✓ DONE at t=19 |
| 19-22 | J1 | J1=1 |
| 22-23 | J1 | J1=0 ✓ DONE at t=23 |

**Results:**
| Job | BT | CT | TAT | WT |
|-----|----|----|-----|----|
| J1 | 10 | 23 | 23 | 13 |
| J2 | 4 | 16 | 16 | 12 |
| J3 | 6 | 19 | 19 | 13 |
| J4 | 3 | 12 | 12 | 9 |

Average TAT = (23+16+19+12)/4 = **17.50**
First to finish = **J4 at t=12**

---

### Compile and Run:
```bash
