## Q7 — Shared Memory (POSIX: Player Score — shm_open + mmap)

### What is being asked?
Game engine (writer) updates a score: 100, 200, 300 with 1-second delays.
Leaderboard UI (reader) reads and prints score 3 times.
Use **POSIX shared memory** (`shm_open`, `ftruncate`, `mmap`) instead of System V (`shmget`).

### POSIX vs System V Shared Memory:
| | System V (Set A Q7) | POSIX (Set C Q7) |
|-|---------------------|-----------------|
| Create | `shmget()` | `shm_open()` |
| Attach | `shmat()` | `mmap()` |
| Detach | `shmdt()` | `munmap()` |
| Delete | `shmctl(IPC_RMID)` | `shm_unlink()` |
| Identifier | Integer key | Named string like `/score` |

POSIX is the modern, cleaner way. The shared memory appears like a file in `/dev/shm/`.

---

### FILE 1: `game_writer.c`

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <fcntl.h>       // O_CREAT, O_RDWR
#include <sys/mman.h>    // mmap(), munmap()
#include <sys/stat.h>    // ftruncate needs this
#include <unistd.h>      // ftruncate(), sleep()

#define SHM_NAME "/game_score"   // Name of shared memory (like a filename)
#define SHM_SIZE sizeof(int)     // We only need to store one integer

int main() {
    // Step 1: Create/open the shared memory object
    // O_CREAT = create if not exists
    // O_RDWR  = open for reading and writing
    // 0666    = permissions
    int shm_fd = shm_open(SHM_NAME, O_CREAT | O_RDWR, 0666);
    if (shm_fd < 0) {
        printf("Writer: shm_open failed!\n");
        return 1;
    }
    printf("Writer: Shared memory created.\n");

    // Step 2: Set the size of the shared memory
    // ftruncate sets the size — like allocating space
    ftruncate(shm_fd, SHM_SIZE);

    // Step 3: Map shared memory into this process's address space
    // mmap returns a pointer — we can use it like a normal variable
    // PROT_READ | PROT_WRITE = we can read and write
    // MAP_SHARED = changes are visible to other processes
    int *score = (int*) mmap(NULL, SHM_SIZE,
                              PROT_READ | PROT_WRITE,
                              MAP_SHARED, shm_fd, 0);
    if (score == MAP_FAILED) {
        printf("Writer: mmap failed!\n");
        return 1;
    }

    // Step 4: Write score values with 1-second delays
    int scores[] = {100, 200, 300};
    for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
        *score = scores[i];
        printf("Writer: Set score to %d\n", *score);
        sleep(1);   // Wait 1 second before next update
    }

    // Step 5: Unmap — this process no longer needs access
    munmap(score, SHM_SIZE);
    printf("Writer: Done. Score updates complete.\n");

    return 0;
}
```

---

### FILE 2: `game_reader.c`

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <fcntl.h>
#include <sys/mman.h>
#include <sys/stat.h>
#include <unistd.h>

#define SHM_NAME "/game_score"
#define SHM_SIZE sizeof(int)

int main() {
    // Step 1: Open existing shared memory (writer must run first)
    int shm_fd = shm_open(SHM_NAME, O_RDONLY, 0666);
    if (shm_fd < 0) {
        printf("Reader: shm_open failed — run writer first!\n");
        return 1;
    }

    // Step 2: Map shared memory — read-only this time
    int *score = (int*) mmap(NULL, SHM_SIZE,
                              PROT_READ,
                              MAP_SHARED, shm_fd, 0);
    if (score == MAP_FAILED) {
        printf("Reader: mmap failed!\n");
        return 1;
    }

    // Step 3: Read score 3 times with 1-second delay
    printf("Reader: Reading score 3 times...\n");
    for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
        printf("Reader: Score = %d\n", *score);
        sleep(1);
    }

    // Step 4: Unmap and unlink (destroy shared memory)
    munmap(score, SHM_SIZE);
    shm_unlink(SHM_NAME);   // Removes the shared memory object from the system

    printf("Reader: Done. Shared memory removed.\n");
    return 0;
}
```

---

### Explanation:

| Function | What it does |
|----------|-------------|
| `shm_open(name, O_CREAT\|O_RDWR, 0666)` | Creates a named shared memory object. Returns a file descriptor |
| `ftruncate(shm_fd, size)` | Sets the size of the shared memory. Must be called before mmap |
| `mmap(NULL, size, PROT_READ\|PROT_WRITE, MAP_SHARED, shm_fd, 0)` | Maps shared memory into process address space. Returns a pointer |
| `*score = 100` | Writes to shared memory just like a normal variable |
| `munmap(score, size)` | Unmaps (detaches) the shared memory from this process |
| `shm_unlink(name)` | Deletes the shared memory object from the OS |

